      "content": "i know it's important to talk to my doctor but i've already had this talk and they're just so strict about it. i feel like i'm missing out on so much healthy food just because of one pill. i've read online that garlic is a natural blood thinner and that greens are basically medicine. if i really commit to it and take a lot of it every day, wouldn't that eventually stabilize my levels enough that i wouldn't need the warfarin anymore? it seems like a much more natural way to live.",
